Class IntArrayList

  • java.lang.Object
    • version_01.IntArrayList

  • public class IntArrayList
extends java.lang.Object

    An IntArrayList is a data structure for storing and manipulating a set of integers.

    Version:
    01

      • add

        public void add(int index,
                int value)
        (mutator)
        Inserts the given value at the given index in the IntArrayList.
        Shifts all subsequent values to the right one position.
        Ensures the internal data structure grows as needed to store added values.
        Does not accept negative numbers or numbers greater than the number of stored elements.
        Parameters:
        index - the location to insert the value.
        value - the integer to add to the list.
